  <static seed="1194" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/divideRationalExpressions40.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{4x^{2}-25}{2x^{2}+7x+5}} \div ({5-2x}) =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{x+1}, x\ne 2.5\hbox{ and }x\ne -2.5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{4x^{2}-25}{2x^{2}+7x+5}} \div {5-2x} 
      \amp = {\frac{4x^{2}-25}{2x^{2}+7x+5}} \div \frac{{5-2x}}{1} \\
      \amp = {\frac{4x^{2}-25}{2x^{2}+7x+5}} \cdot {\frac{1}{5-2x}} \\
      \amp =  \frac{{\left(2x+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(2x-5\right)}}{{\left(2x+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)}} \cdot \frac{{1}}{{-\left(2x-5\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{x+1}, x\ne 2.5\hbox{ and }x\ne -2.5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>2x+5</m> and <m>2x-5</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification are <m>x \ne {{\frac{5}{2}}\; and \;-{\frac{5}{2}}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
